For {= author =}+ authors, name each author's latest paper according to a scholarly profile, publication list, or aggregator page, and supply a source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per author).

Requirements:
- The page must be clearly scoped to the claimed author — a profile page, publication list, or aggregator entry about this specific researcher. Paper pages that merely include the author in a multi-author byline don't count.
- The claimed paper title (or a close match) must appear on the fetched page content.
- The page must make the recency claim explicit or strongly inferable — paper at the top of a date-sorted publication list, labelled "latest" / "most recent", or a dated ordered list where the claimed paper has the most recent date. Year-grouped lists (entries grouped by year heading with no intra-year ordering) count: any entry in the topmost year-group qualifies. Relevance-sorted lists or pages where recency cannot be inferred don't count.
